Two people were killed, and three were injured, in a tragic
car accident involving two cars on Umlaas Road near Pietermaritzburg on Sunday
morning. Robert McKenzie, spokesperson for KZN EMS, said one person
suffered minor injuries, two people were critically injured and two were
declared dead at the scene. Mark Winterboer, from Midlands EMS, said the two people who
died were travelling together in one car. He said when paramedics arrived at
the scene, the two were entrapped in their car. One had already died, and the
second person died while emergency workers were trying to extract him out of
the wrecked car.